    <p> A good rule of thumb here is to think of the tensor product as the mechanism to combine
      elements in a quantum circuit <em>vertically</em>: two qubits that sit vertically next to each
      other, or two quantum operations that sit vertically next to each other in our circuit
      diagram. </p> -->
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="sec_qops_in_series" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>Combining Quantum Operations in Series</title>

    <p>Vector notation gives us another powerful tool: we can combine gates in series in a circuit.
      We use matrix multiplication to combine operations!</p>

    <p>
      <term>More to come soon...</term>
    </p>
  </subsection>
</section>
